                <head>173. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>According to his own account, Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_MH1"
                        >Macmillan</persName> met in turn with each of the other Heads of
                    Government, beginning at 6 p.m. with President <persName corresp="#p_dGC1">de
                        Gaulle</persName>. At 7:15 p.m., he talked with President <persName
                        corresp="#p_EDD1">Eisenhower</persName>, after which he discussed the summit
                    conference with <persName corresp="#p_KNS1">Khrushchev</persName>. For
                    McMillan’s account of these meetings, see <hi rend="italic">Pointing the
                        Way</hi>, pages 207–208. The meeting with <persName corresp="#p_EDD1"
                        >Eisenhower</persName> is mentioned briefly in <persName corresp="#p_EDD1"
                        >Eisenhower</persName>, <hi rend="italic">Strictly Personal</hi>, page 275.
                    For <persName corresp="#p_KNS1">Khrushchev</persName>’s account of his
                    conversation with <persName corresp="#p_MH1">Macmillan</persName>, see <hi
                        rend="italic">
                        <persName corresp="#p_KNS1">Khrushchev</persName> Remembers: The Last
                        Testament</hi>, pages 459–460.</p>
            </div>
